<Window x:Class="MergersAcquisitions.FormingACorporation"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:MergersAcquisitions"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="FormingACorporation" Height="703.5" Width="1352" MaxWidth="1352" MaxHeight="704">
    <Window.Background>
        <LinearGradientBrush EndPoint="0.5,1" StartPoint="0.5,0">
            <GradientStop Color="Black" Offset="0"/>
            <GradientStop Color="{DynamicResource {x:Static SystemColors.ActiveCaptionColorKey}}" Offset="1"/>
        </LinearGradientBrush>
    </Window.Background>
    <Grid MaxHeight="673" MaxWidth="1344">
        <RichTextBox HorizontalAlignment="Left" Height="640" Margin="13,12,0,0" VerticalAlignment="Top" Width="1322" FontSize="16">
            <FlowDocument>
                <Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" Margin="0,13.33,0,0" TextAlignment="Left">
                    <Run Foreground="#FF4F81BD" Text="Forming the "/>
                    <Run Foreground="#FF4F81BD" FontFamily="Calibri" Text="Corporation"/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,16,0,0" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontFamily="Calibri" Text="For non-profits the organization can be a corporation, unincorporated association or a charitable trust.  The main reason to incorporate the association would be so that the founders are protected from any personal liability from the association's operations, costs and actions. The corporation's legal name will be National Association for Elementary and Middle School Education in Technology and Science Incorporated. The name will have been cleared by the secretary of state for any conflicts.  The articles of incorporation listing its bylaws and mission statement which would qualify it for a tax exempt status from the IRS will be submitted to the State Corporation Commission (SCC) in MA along with the appropriate fees. It will also provide an annual report and registered office location to the SCC. The non-profit will apply for and maintain a 501(c)(3) status. This status will qualify it for a tax-exempt status, be eligible to receive public and private grant money, it can also solicit for tax-deductible donations, proceed with fundraisers and limit personal liability for its members. Since it is a non-profit it will not issue any stock or any dividends. The articles of incorporation will include name, purpose, limitations such as all the earnings below to the corporation and will not engage in any unlawful activity, it will be a member based non-profit corporation, names of directors and rules for dissolution will also be included in the articles of incorporation."/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,16,0,0" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontFamily="Calibri" Text="Bylaws for the corporation will be developed. It will include name, location, purpose, power and duties, number, election term, qualifications, development, communication policies, vacancies, meetings and voting rights for the board of directors. It should also include information about number of officers and agents, elections and terms. Information about the different types of committees of the board such as executive committee, committee chairs, nominating board development committee, Audit and personnel committee will be included in the bylaws document. Articles of indemnification of officers and directors towards state and federal laws will be included.  Conflict of interest, disclosure, account book and minutes, fiscal year audit, loans, amendments to bylaws will be addressed as well in the bylaws certificate."/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,16,0,0" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontFamily="Calibri" Text="The organization will be incorporated in the Greater Boston area with initial funding approved by federal grant along with fund raisers, donations and partnerships from private educational institutions and local employers. The state of incorporation will be MA versus CA or Delaware because of the large pool of higher level educational institutes within the greater Boston area. "/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,13.33" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontFamily="Calibri"/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,13.33" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontFamily="Calibri" Text="A board of directors will be recruited by the founders of the member based non-profit corporation from the pool of stake holders and prominent members. A small governing board of up to 12 members which will make decisions related to the policies and operations of the corporation will be created. Broad range skill set such as business, communications, finances, fundraising, employment history and or detailed knowledge of K-12 curriculum would be needed in the governing board. Separate from the governing a small advisory board consisting of Babson professors, other successfully non-profit entrepreneurs, student and teacher representatives will also be formed. The advisory board can provide guidance and advice to the governing board.   A mission statement will be formed with the help of the board of directors and will be used to market the organization to attract more volunteers.  The individuals serving on the board must oblige to the bylaws of the corporate and always act in the interest of the corporation.   As the corporation matures the size of the board directors can gradually increase, rotations of terms will be implemented, where half of the members stay and the remaining are replaced by new members on a 3-5 year basis. A well developed orientation program will be put in place for the new members. The program will involve learning about the mission, bylaws and finances of the corporation.  The membership based organization will have regular monthly board meetings to amend the bylaws in the initial stages.  The meetings held by the board of directors will result in strategic and financial planning for the corporation. "/>
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph FontFamily="Times New Roman" Margin="0,0,0,13.33" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontFamily="Calibri" Text="The association will create collaborations with local schools it will develop its policies and activities with a trial and error process along with feedback from the educational institutional and then gradually expand the network of educational institutes and working professionals throughout the nation.   "/>
                </Paragraph>
            </FlowDocument>
        </RichTextBox>

    </Grid>
</Window>
